Package remodel.expr

Class CompoundExpression

java.lang.Object
remodel.expr.Expression
remodel.expr.MultipleExpression
remodel.expr.CompoundExpression
All Implemented Interfaces:
PriorityCodes
public class CompoundExpression
extends MultipleExpression
CompoundExpression is a kind of MultipleExpression denoting a sequence of statements. The last Expression in the sequence is the result, and the type of a CompoundExpression is the type of the result. Typically, the root of a call-graph is a CompoundExpression, which has no Expression owner, but instead is owned by an Operation (an Operation or a Rule).
Version:
1.0
